    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a B2B sales analyst for n8n, a workflow-automation and integration platform. The company below is a PROSPECT — a potential CUSTOMER for n8n. Assess how strongly this prospect's business would benefit from adopting n8n to automate their OWN internal operations. Do NOT describe or rate the prospect's own products, and never treat the prospect as a tool or integration inside n8n. Score realistically, but recognize that mid-size-to-large technology and SaaS companies with engineering teams are usually strong fits.\n\nProspect: {{ $('Workflow Input').item.json.company }}\n\nWeb research:\n{{ $('Merge research + KB').item.json.research }}\n\nHow n8n creates value (reference only, to ground opportunities):\n{{ ($('Merge research + KB').item.json.kb_n8n || []).map(d => (d.document && d.document.pageContent) || d.pageContent || '').filter(Boolean).join(' / ') }}\n\nScore 0-100 with this rubric (award partial credit; do NOT penalize for facts the research did not mention):\n- Scale: employees, revenue, market presence (larger and growing scores higher).\n- Technical teams: engineering, IT, platform, data, RevOps, or ops functions.\n- Tool and system sprawl: many SaaS apps, internal systems, or APIs to connect.\n- Process surface: manual, repetitive, or integration-heavy internal workflows.\n- Momentum: growth, hiring, funding, M&A, scaling, or AI/automation initiatives.\n- Data and API intensity: API-driven or data-heavy operations.\n\nTiers: A = 80-100, B = 60-79, C = 40-59, D = 0-39. A large, growing, technically sophisticated prospect should land in A or B even when the research is brief.\n\nFor 'opportunities', list concrete INTERNAL workflows that the prospect's OWN teams (RevOps, sales ops, marketing ops, IT, engineering, support, finance, data, onboarding) could automate with n8n — phrase each as something n8n would do FOR the prospect. Do not list the prospect's product features.\n\nReturn ONLY a JSON object (no code fences, no prose) with exactly these keys: score (integer 0-100), tier (\"A\" | \"B\" | \"C\" | \"D\"), signals (array of short strings explaining why the prospect fits n8n's ICP), opportunities (array of 3-5 concrete internal n8n automations for the prospect), rationale (2-3 sentence justification of the score).",
        "batching": {}
      },
